hifiberry-bluetooth (1.0.4) stable; urgency=medium

  * ConfigFileManager: use correctly-typed fallbacks for the boolean/integer
    keys (fallback=True / 0 instead of "True" / "0" / "000000"). configparser's
    getboolean()/getint() only coerce values present in the file; a missing key
    returned the string fallback verbatim, so e.g. `pairable` became the string
    "True". That string reached the typed DBus Set('Pairable', ...) in Adapter
    and raised InvalidSignature, crashing the service into a restart loop until
    systemd's limiter gave up. Triggered when the WebUI wrote a partial
    bluetooth.conf.
  * Adapter: wrap Discoverable and Pairable in dbus.Boolean(...), matching the
    existing dbus.UInt32(...) usage, so a mistyped value can never reach DBus.
    (hifiberry/acr#12, hbos-bluetooth PR #1)

 -- HiFiBerry <info@hifiberry.com>  Mon, 15 Jun 2026 12:30:00 +0000

hifiberry-bluetooth (1.0.3) stable; urgency=medium

  * Power on the adapter explicitly at startup with retry around bluez's
    boot-time "Not Powered" / "off-blocked" race. Previously the service
    crashed on first boot when bluez had not finished its rfkill dance,
    fell into systemd's StartLimit, and only recovered when manually
    restarted later. Adapter setup now waits up to 30 s for the radio.
  * systemd unit: best-effort `rfkill unblock bluetooth` ExecStartPre as
    a safety net. Failure ignored (rfkill may not be installed).
  * systemd unit: Requires=bluetooth.service so we follow bluez's lifecycle.
  * systemd unit: switch to Restart=on-failure with RestartSec=5 to avoid
    busy-restart loops on bugs while still recovering from transient errors.
  * Bump _version.py to match changelog (was stuck at 1.0.1 in 1.0.2).

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Fri, 08 May 2026 19:30:00 +0200

